(Pilgrim Optimizer CLI: First Commands) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Purpose) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This guide explains the first three CLI commands in `pilgrim-optimizer` and what they ) Tj
T*
(currently prove in the Ruleset A mancala sandbox.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The goal is to make the early loop explicit:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(`scenario -> validate -> legal actions -> search -> recommendation`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Prerequisites) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Python 3.12+ installed \(`python3 --version`\)) Tj
T*
(- Project dependencies installed from repository root:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(python3 -m pip install -e ".[dev]") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- You are in the repository root:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(cd /path/to/pilgrim-optimizer) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Command 1: Validate a scenario) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(python3 -m pilgrim.cli validate scenarios/mancala_sandbox_001.json) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What it does right now:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Loads the scenario JSON file.) Tj
T*
(- Parses it and loads the linked setup/config JSON files.) Tj
T*
(- Checks simplified mancala-sandbox invariants.) Tj
T*
(- Confirms the scenario is a valid starting state for the current engine.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What it does **not** do:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- It does not solve the game.) Tj
T*
(- It does not prove full Pilgrim rules are implemented.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Typical output:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Scenario 'mancala_sandbox_001' is valid.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Command 2: List legal actions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(python3 -m pilgrim.cli legal-actions scenarios/mancala_sandbox_001.json) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What it does right now:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Loads the same scenario.) Tj
T*
(- Asks the current rules engine to generate legal actions for the active player and phase.) Tj
ET
endstream
