(- Prints stable, readable action IDs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- It is one of the fastest ways to debug action generation.) Tj
T*
(- It should usually be checked before trusting solver output.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Example output:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(sow:0:1->2->3) Tj
T*
(sow:0:5->6->7) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Command 3: Run the simple solver) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(python3 -m pilgrim.cli solve scenarios/mancala_sandbox_001.json --depth 3) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What it does right now:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Runs the current exact-search prototype.) Tj
T*
(- Searches to the specified depth \(`--depth 3` in this example\).) Tj
T*
(- Uses a temporary placeholder evaluation function.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Example output:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(best_score=3) Tj
T*
(best_action=sow:0:1->2->3) Tj
T*
(nodes_expanded=27) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How to interpret the current output) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- `best_score` is a value under the **temporary placeholder evaluation**, not true final ) Tj
T*
(Pilgrim VP.) Tj
T*
(- `best_action=sow:0:1->2->3` means sow from city to north, north_east, east.) Tj
T*
(- `nodes_expanded` is how many search nodes were explored.) Tj
T*
(- Together, this confirms the current development loop works end-to-end:) Tj
T*
(  `scenario -> validate -> legal actions -> search -> recommendation`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Position mapping used by the current sandbox:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- `0 = city`) Tj
T*
(- `1 = north`) Tj
T*
(- `2 = north_east`) Tj
T*
(- `3 = east`) Tj
T*
(- `4 = south_east`) Tj
T*
(- `5 = south`) Tj
T*
(- `6 = south_west`) Tj
T*
(- `7 = west`) Tj
T*
(- `8 = north_west`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What this does not mean yet) Tj
ET
